Cape weed
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the English catsear, esp. in Cant.;a) a weed of sandy soils and dry open pasture; b) (formerly) in Cant., cat's ear; often =Cape daisy [(check also Cape tulip) and cf W3] [x-ref only now at weed].
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
