Citations
Date: 0/0/1898
Source: Merriam-Webster Third International
Author:
Vol / Page: 2019
Edition:
Quote: <i>Cape.weed.</i> (k&amacr.p.w&emacr.d.), <i>n. (Bot.)</i> A composite plant (<i>Cryptostemma calendulaceum</i>) allied to the marigold. It is a native of South Africa (the Cape). Introduced into Australia, it has spread over every pasture, and in the springtime its blossoms make yellow all the landscape. The <i>Capeweed</i> of Europe is a lichen (<i>Rocella tinctoria</i>) from the Cape Verde Islands.
