Quote: <i>Cape Weed</i> In Europe, <i>Roccella tinctoria</i>, a lichen from the Cape de Verde Islands, from which a dye is produced. In New Zealand, name given to the European cats-ear, <i>Hypaechoris radicata</i>. In Australia it is as in quotation below. [1878 <i>Cryptostemma calendulaceum</i>]
