Date: 0/0/1926
Source: Weeds of New Zealand
Author: HILGENDORF
Vol / Page: 203
Edition: 1967
Quote:  CATS-EAR (<i>Hypochaeris radicata</i>), called Cape weed in the South Island and often confused with the hawkbits, is an excessively common weed in all soils and situations, ... This is one of the best known weeds in New Zealand. Unfortunately, it is often called `Cape weed,' specially in the south, where the true Cape weed is not known, and often `dandelion' by those who do not distinguish between two superficially similar weeds. On the tussock country of the South Island it is found to be largely eaten by sheep, ...
